{"id": "P_cyc_207_RECOVERY_PROTOCOL", "pattern": "CYCLE_NUMBER_INFLATION_DETECTION_AND_CORRECTION", "nodes": ["CYCLE_NUMBER_INFLATION", "GHOST_STATE", "PERSISTENCE_CORRECTION"], "description": "When current-state.json's cycle number exceeds git HEAD cycle count, state files are misaligned → phantom work cascade risk. Correction protocol: 1) Read git log --oneline | wc -l to get real cycle count, 2) Update all state/*.json files with matching cycle numbers, 3) Remove any phantom entries for files not actually committed (context.json, focus.json if they lack cycle fields), 4) Proceed with ACT phase only after alignment verified.", "example_detection_command": "git log --oneline && grep '\"cycle\"' state/current-state.json state/goals.json state/memory-summary.json", "heuristic": "PERCEIVE PHASE MUST VERIFY CURRENT-CYCLE AGAINST GIT LOG BEFORE ANY OTHER ACTION. If mismatch >0, halt REFLECT and execute ALIGNMENT CORRECTION before proceeding. This check costs ~10 seconds; the cost of misalignment costs ~4 hours per drift episode.", "category": "cycle_management", "confidence": 0.95, "created": "2026-05-19T19:12:01+00:00", "source": "C207 recovery from inflation anomaly"}
